title:  "A big change. MultiMachineBuilder 1a1 will not load saves from 0.x"
---

After a long period of development and testing, MultiMachineBuilder is taking a **major step forward**. The upcoming release, **1a1**, introduces a completely new engine architecture — which means **it will not load saves from any 0.x version**.

## Why the break?

MultiMachineBuilder has grown beyond its original design. To support more complex worlds, modding capabilities, and future expansion, we needed to:

- Switch block, item, and part types to **immutable data structures**
- Move from flat-file saves to a **relational + document-based world storage**
- Enable **world-specific mods, textures, and sounds**
- Introduce a clean separation between **core blocks** and **mod-added polymorphic blocks**
- Improve handler systems for **power, items, fluids, and signals**

These changes are fundamental, and keeping compatibility with old 0.x saves would compromise engine stability and prevent the new features from being fully realized.

## What’s new in 1a1

- **Immutable block, item, and part types** for safer and cleaner code
- **Relational database for core world data** and **JSON document storage for polymorphic blocks**
- **Per-world mod and asset support** (textures, sounds, scripts)
- **Improved handler system** for power, fluid, item, and signal connections
- **Versioned save files** with a new file extension to clearly separate them from old saves
- **Pipes now can have modules attached**
- **Hangable wires** for early crossings.
- **Reworked power system** with more tiers. Now only SLV and ULV. Planned hierarchy:
  - SLV - Super Low Voltage
  - ULV - Ultra Low Voltage
  - VLV - Very Low Voltage
  -  LV - Low Voltage
  -  MV - Medium Voltage
  -  HV - High Voltage
  -  EV - Extreme Voltage
  -  IV - Insane Voltage
  - LuV - Ludicrous Voltage
  -  UV - Ultimate Voltage
  -  PV - Penultimate Voltage
  -  XV - Exavoltage
  -  ZV - Zettavoltage
  -  YV - Yottavoltage
  -  RV - Ronnavoltage
  -  QV - Quettavoltage

## What this means for players

- Existing 0.x saves **cannot be loaded** in 1a1.  
- Every new world will use the new engine and save format.  
- Mods and assets are now **world-specific**, allowing different worlds to run different mods independently.  
- The upgrade ensures **cleaner, faster, and more extensible worlds** for future development.

## Moving forward

This is a **fresh start**. While it means leaving old worlds behind, it also unlocks **powerful new possibilities** for modding, multi-system interactions, and long-term stability. We are committed to building a **strong foundation** for MultiMachineBuilder’s next evolution.

We recommend backing up your 0.x worlds if you wish to preserve them, but know that they will remain **incompatible** with the new engine.

Thank you for your support, and we’re excited to see what you create with **1a1**!